                    "SS2_ITEM_HITLIST_NAME":  "HitList",
                    "SS2_ITEM_RELICOFECHELON_PICKUP":  "Gain a massive buff on equipment use. \u003cstyle=cDeath\u003eUsing an equipment permanently increases its cooldown\u003c/style\u003e.",
                    "SS2_NEMCOMMANDO_SECONDARY_BEAM_DESCRIPTION":  "\u003cstyle=cIsDamage\u003eGouging\u003c/style\u003e. Fire a \u003cstyle=cIsDamage\u003epiercing\u003c/style\u003e sword beam for \u003cstyle=cIsDamage\u003e400% damage\u003c/style\u003e.",
                    "SS2_PYRO_DESCRIPTION":  "The Pyro is a survivor who excels in crowd control, torching pests with fury and precision.",
                    "SS2_ACHIEVEMENT_CHIRR_MAID_NAME":  "Chirr: Cleaning Up",
                    "SS2_ACHIEVEMENT_NEMESIS_MERCENARY_CLONE_NAME":  "Nemesis Mercenary: Duped",
                    "SS2_NEMCAPTAIN_ORDERREDUCE_NAME":  "ORDER: Administer Stimulant",
                    "SS2_ITEM_WATCHMETRONOME_LORE":  "Order: Broken Watch Metronome\nTracking Number: 88******\nEstimated Delivery: 04/14/2056:\nShipping Method: Priority\nShipping Address: 33 Skyview Drive, Albumen, Venus\nShipping Details:\n\nHey, this is the watch metronome I told you needed fixing. Apparently, the things been falling outta whack for a couple weeks now, and me and the boys can\u0027t get any recording done with it speeding up all the time. I\u0027d like it back fairly quickly, since usin\u0027 the in-ear metronome hurts my ears if it\u0027s in for too long. Oh, and be careful with it, too. The watch is a gift from my pops, and it really means a lot to me. Thanks a bunch in advance!\n",
                    "SS2_UNLOCKABLE_LOG_ACIDBUG":  "Logbook: Archer Bug",
                    "SS2_EXECUTIONER_AXE_NAME":  "Execution",
                    "SS2_MULE_KEYWORD_OVERCLOCKING":  "\u003cstyle=cKeywordName\u003eOverclocking\u003c/style\u003e\u003c/style=cSub\u003eHold the button to extend the skill\u0027s duration, but also extend the skill\u0027s cooldown length.\u003c/sub\u003e",
                    "SS2_MULE_PUNCH_NAME":  "Interference Removal",
                    "SS2_NEMMANDO_SPECIAL_SCEPBOSS_NAME":  "Judgement Cut",
                    "SS2_BORG_NAME":  "Borg",
                    "SS2_NEMMANDO_OUTRO_FAILURE":  "..and so he returned, concluding his endless struggle.",
                    "SS2_ITEM_VOIDROCK_DESC":  "Be hunted by \u003cstyle=cDeath\u003eNemesis Survivors\u003c/style\u003e.",
                    "SS2_ITEM_CRYPTICSOURCE_LORE":  "",
                    "SS2_DIFFICULTY_TYPHOON_DESC":  "Maximum challenge. The world is a nightmare, and survival is merely an illusion. Nobody has what it takes.\u003cstyle=cStack\u003e\n\n\u003ePlayer Health Regeneration: \u003cstyle=cIsHealth\u003e-40%\u003c/style\u003e\n\u003eDifficulty Scaling: \u003cstyle=cIsHealth\u003e+75%\u003c/style\u003e\n\u003eMonster Spawn Limit: \u003cstyle=cIsHealth\u003e+100%\u003c/style\u003e\n\u003eMonster Spawn Rate: \u003cstyle=cIsHealth\u003e+25%\u003c/style\u003e\n\u003eGold and Experience Rewards: \u003cstyle=cisHealth\u003e-20%\u003c/style\u003e",
                    "SS2_NEMEXECUTIONER_UTILITY_NAME":  "fear",
                    "SS2_SKIN_NEMESIS_MERCENARY_GRANDMASTERY":  "[NYI] Corporate",
                    "SS2_SHRINE_ETHEREAL_HINT_GOLEMPLAINS":  "High atop the cliff.",
                    "SS2_EXECUTIONER_SUBTITLE":  "Dreaded Guillotine",
                    "SS2_CLAYMONGER_BODY_LORE":  "These are literally pets and livestock of people who fell to the tar... you monster... :c",
                    "SS2_ITEM_BLASTKNUCKLES_LORE":  "\"Best fight I ever won\"\n    - One-Arm Larry",
                    "SS2_ITEM_JETBOOTS_LORE":  "Record for the postmortem of Hephaestus Metal Works\n\nLocation: Hephaestus Metal Works, Mars\nLocation Status: Interior destroyed via fire\nCasualties: The owner, via fire\nOn Site Report:\n\nI\u0027d assumed the cause of the fire was the work of a forge, furnace, or even a cigarette break. There wasn\u0027t much different from any other workshop of the same niche. A bunch of old kinds of swords, armor, farming equipment, et cetera. Though it would seem the forget was a hobbyist himself, as there were what looked to be some projects you normally wouldn\u0027t find there in the back.\n\nA fair amount of them were nothing more than motors and metal. He seemed to practice making clockwork. But he eventually moved on to fuel and engine based items. Old lawn mowers, motor cycles, and generators. He eventually moved on to propulsion systems. Small remote planes, helicopters, an old rusty jetpack. It seemed he was working up to something, and we found what it was in the back.\n\nThere was clearly some genius behind him. He was building a pair of jet boots from scratch. They haven\u0027t entered production before, since jetpacks do the job fine, and boots can\u0027t be as sturdy and heavy while getting the same amount of thrust. He seemed to have the same thought, as he made them more sturdy for his protection, but tried to compensate by turning up the output on the thrust. The result ended in the heat building up and erupting from below him. Unfortunately, his inventive nature cost him his business and his life.\n\nThe surrounding area didn\u0027t take any damage so the shop may be renovated soon. The boots have been confiscated and are en route to be studied and decommissioned, and the remaining items from inside the shop have been sent to their next of kin.\n\nThis concludes my report.\n",
                    "SS2_ITEM_HOTTESTSAUCE_LORE":  "\u003cstyle=cMono\u003e//--Auto-Transcription from room K3 (Kitchen, 3rd Floor) of Kaymar Hotel--//\u003c/style\u003e\n\nA tall, thin man walks into the room, holding a large cardboard box. \"Hey, CHEF. How\u0027s it going?\" He sets the box on the counter. \"Alright, we\u0027ve got a bunch of new sauces you\u0027ll have to get accustomed with. I\u0027ll walk you through them now, if you don\u0027t mind.\" The CHEF bot gives him its attention, but continues to work.\n\nThe man proceeds down the rows of various colored bottles, explaining to the CHEF their names, flavors, and uses in cooking. Eventually, he stops at a red-colored bottle, and hesitates briefly.\n\n\"...Okay, now. This bottle? It\u0027s unlabelled for a reason. If you get a meal order stating that you use \"\u003cstyle=cDeath\u003eHottest Sauce\u003c/style\u003e\" on it, you go ahead and use this bottle. But do NOT use it under ANY OTHER CIRCUMSTANCES. I know sometimes you need to improvise to finish a dish, but you should NEVER use this bottle if you\u0027re doing that. Do you understand?\"\n\nThe CHEF bot, still working, nods affirmatively.\n\n\"Good. I expect great things from you, CHEF.\"\n\nThe CHEF bot nods once again, and briefly pauses its work to put the bottles in the appropriate locations.\n\n\"...Oh, and also?\"\n\nThe CHEF bot pauses to give its attention to the man once more.\n\n\"Please, don\u0027t break that bottle. I know you\u0027re a robot and all, but I also know that accidents happen, and that particular accident might leave a hole in the floor.\"\n\nThe CHEF bot gazes at the bottle briefly, before carefully setting it in the back of the cupboard with the rest of the sauces.",
                    "SS2_DRONE_SHOCK_SKILL_DESCRIPTION":  "Fires an electric blast, dealing \u003cstyle=cIsDamage\u003e100% damage\u003c/style\u003e in an area and \u003cstyle=cIsUtility\u003eshocking\u003c/style\u003e enemies for \u003cstyle=cIsUtility\u003e5 seconds\u003c/style\u003e.",
                    "SS2_ACHIEVEMENT_TOYSOLDIERS_DESC":  "As Captain, recruit 15 minions at one time.",
                    "SS2_ITEM_REMUNERATION_FAILURE":  "\u003ccolor=#f4adfa\u003e\u003clink=\"textWavy\"\u003eHow memorable...\u003c/link\u003e\u003c/color\u003e",
