                    "SS2_BIRTHRIGHT_UNCLAIMED":  "\u003cstyle=cShrine\u003e{0} lacks what they seek.\u003c/style\u003e",
                    "SS2_ACHIEVEMENT_UNIVERSALCHARGER_NAME":  "tRet 12 Pro Max Plus",
                    "SS2_NEMCOMMANDO_SUBTITLE":  "Lone Echo",
                    "SS2_NEMCOMMANDO_UTILITY_TAUNT_DESCRIPTION":  "\u003cstyle=cIsHealth\u003eTaunt\u003c/style\u003e nearby enemies, decreasing their \u003cstyle=cIsDamage\u003earmor\u003c/style\u003e but increasing their \u003cstyle=cIsDamage\u003edamage\u003c/style\u003e. Can be held to stack the effect up to \u003cstyle=cIsDamage\u003e3\u003c/style\u003e times.",
                    "SS2_MULE_JUMP_DESC":  "\u003cstyle=cIsUtility\u003eHold to charge\u003c/style\u003e a powerful upwards leap.",
                    "SS2_TRADER_BODY_NAME":  "Zanzan the Faded",
                    "SS2_ITEM_LOWQUALITYSPEAKERS_NAME":  "Low Quality Speakers",
                    "SS2_NEMEXECUTIONER_SPECIAL_ALT_DESCRIPTION":  "fly and buff and duration on kill",
                    "SS2_ITEM_SCRAPFROMCHEST_PICKUP":  "Chests drop extra scrap.",
                    "SS2_PLAYER_ARMOR_DEFAULT_NAME_TOKEN":  "Default Damage Received",
                    "SS2_PYRO_LORE":  "Buzzing, buzzing, and more buzzing. As they tried to go over the final details of the job, the droning of insect wings was the only sound to break through - but it didnâ€™t matter. The job was simple, and he knew how to see it through properly. The woman in the hardhat proceeded back to the port as the man in polymeric fibers equipped a sizable weapon from his back. Clutching it firmly in one hand, he used the other to manage the cargo bay doors, bracing himself for the swarm within.\n\nA suffocating miasma of acid filled the air as the doors slid open. If not for his respirator, the fumes wouldâ€™ve been unbearable, toxic enough to knock him out within minutes. The thick air was populated with countless giant green bugs, busily flying between corroded containers and the hive structures theyâ€™d built between them. Their incessant droning drowned out his thoughts - just the way he liked it. None of the insects took notice of the intruder until a torrent of napalm exploded into a blaze. \n\nWarriors descended as workers scattered, though it was too late for all of them. The ones quick enough to form an offense merely hastened their demise, falling to his feet as the fire devoured them. Napalm clung indiscriminately to nest, pest, and security chest alike as he slowly weaved his way between the labyrinth of cargo that laid out the foundations of the lair. Black smoke began to fill the bay, thickening with each step he took, while the ground piled high with charred remains. More than anything, though, it was the heat - the relentless, searing heat of his cleaning flames - that filled the room. Shipping containers turned into furnaces, and the bay a graveyard as he systematically purged the infestation.\n\nHours later, little was left but the acrid stench of decay, the occasional mandible or thorax, and a fine layer of ash carpeting the floor. After a third lap around the bay, he finally found what heâ€™d been searching for, stashed away behind cracked container doors in the darkest corner of the room: an unharmed nest of eggs. He chuckled to himself, closing the cracked door and submerging the eggs back into darkness. As the large bay doors slammed shut, the woman in the helmet wrinkled her nose, handing him payment for a job well done. And a job well done it was - one hundred percent of the live bugs reduced to an easy clean-up.\n\nAs he left the dock, he thought about the bonus heâ€™d claimed for himself: the eggs, healthily growing in their ideal conditions, where regulation couldnâ€™t look until it was too late. There would never be a job as enjoyable as them.",
                    "SS2_ITEM_INSECTICIDE_LORE":  "Return: REAVE Insect Killer Aerosol 400g (8)\nTracking Number: 3528*******\nEstimated Delivery: 1/6/2056\nShipping Method: Standard\nShipping Address: 299 Umbrella Way, Itoki Fluctus, Venus\nReason For Return:\n\nProduct arrived damaged. Five cans have noticable physical damage and deformities, two to the point of leakage. One is completely burst. I\u0027ve seen your commercials and knowing what that stuff\u0027s capable of leaves me thinking it\u0027d best be disposed of by your experts, on your dime.\n\nI\u0027ll be expecting a refund on this as well.",
                    "SS2_ITEM_NKOTASHERITAGE_LORE":  "\"My friends. I have gathered you all here today to share some important news.\n\nFirst, it pains my heart to announce that Nkota, the last of our great leaders, our kind matriarch, has sadly passed on from this life. As far as we know, she took her last breath peacefully in rest last night, full of years and with all business here finished. With that said, there shall be no one to succeed her in leadership. She was the last of her line, with no living brothers, sisters, or children.\n\nInstead, in her final testament, her wisdom has created a new beginning. For us. For all of us. Her wish is that the remaining members of this community spread out, either together or separately, into the world. It is perhaps a drastic option, but one that I, personally, also believe to be the best for this community.\n\nNkota shall be buried at our final destination, as is her will. You all may grieve for her and this community for a time, but do not tarry. A group of pilgrims will travel with myself to the great grey path, fifty miles west, after a week\u0027s time. You may follow, or go on your own way. It is your choice entirely. If you do not think that you can make the journey, do not fret. Nkota may have had no children, yes, but her heritage is in spirit, not in blood. You are all her children, and she will protect you until you reach your final goal.\n\nThank you all for your time. I would suggest you begin to pack your possessions for the journey ahead.\"\n\n - Eulogy for Nkota and the Village of Dago",
                    "SS2_EVENT_GLACIALELITE_START":  "A glacial wind blows in...",
                    "SS2_BROTHER_KILL_CHIRR":  "Join your sisters.",
